HEADWORD: androus
<hw>*an"drous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>'anh`r</grk>,
<grk>'andro`s</grk>, a man.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A terminal
combining form: Having a stamen or stamens; staminate; <as>as,
mon<ex>androus</ex>, with one stamen; poly<ex>androus</ex>, with many
stamens.</as></def>⟦br⟧
